{"履修期": "春学期", "主な教授言語": "英語", "授業目的": "Different disaster cases either in Japan or in Taiwan will be discussed in\nclass. There are different disasters happened each year such as typhoons\n(hurricanes), mudslides, flooding, earthquakes, and so on. Tainan City experienced\nheavy rainfall in July of 2024. There were three consecutive days off announced\nby Tainan City Government owing to the heavy rainfall. And northern Taiwan had\nserious flooding. In addition, both Taiwan and Japan had earthquake in 2024\nsuch as 0403’s Hualien’s Earthquake and 0101’s Noto’s Earthquake. The purpose\nof this course is to introduce the role of disaster management system. It\nincludes normative and descriptive perspectives. Owing to climate change, some\ndisasters could be expected such as sea level rise and global warming. The\npurpose of this course is to enable students to be familiar with theories and\npractice of disaster management. Basic theories of disaster management\nincluding bureaucracy are also introduced in this class. Disasters include\ntyphoons (or hurricane), flood, earthquake, tsunami, and so on. Students are\nrequired to understand theories and know how to use theories as tools to deal\nwith issues and problems of disasters.", "到達目標": "Learning by doing through models and theories", "特記事項": "", "関連科目": "organizational behavior, management courses", "授業の概要・背景": "disasters happened unexpectedly", "授業方法": "startup with online (on-demand format). Face to face are the main type for this course", "トピック": {"第1回": ["<div><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">【Startup Week】 Online class（On-demand format)《60minutes》class introduction</span></div><div><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0224px;\">&nbsp;Online class（On-demand format)《30minutes》- Analysis of Premier Takaichi's disaster management performance</span></span></div>Introduction of Disaster Management System&nbsp;", ""], "第2回": ["<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" times=\"times\" new=\"